					<p><span class="emphasis">Hypocrite</span> as used in the New Testament may be translated from the Greek as “pretender”; “the Greek word means ‘a play actor,’ or ‘one who feigns, represents dramatically, or exaggerates a part’” (<a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/6.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matthew 6:2</a>, footnote <span class="emphasis">a</span>). If we do not give others the opportunity to change at their own pace, we are simply pretending to be Latter-day Saints.</p>
